.\" Man page for backport-subsystem
.TH BACKPORT-SUBSYSTEM 1 "June 2026" "backport-subsystem" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
backport-subsystem \- automated RHEL kernel subsystem backport
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B backport-subsystem
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.PP
Must be run from inside a RHEL kernel git repository.
Session parameters are prompted interactively on first run and
reused automatically on subsequent runs.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B backport-subsystem
cherry-picks upstream Linux kernel commits for a given subsystem into a
RHEL or CentOS Stream kernel tree.
It discovers relevant scope paths (source directories, headers,
documentation, device-tree bindings), finds the divergence point
between upstream and RHEL, filters out already-applied commits, and
applies the remaining ones with gort-style commit messages suitable
for RHEL merge requests.
.PP
Out-of-scope files touched by tree-wide commits are automatically
excluded.
In-scope conflicts are resolved according to the selected
.BR \-\-conflict\-policy :
.B patchpal
(launch the
.BR patchpal (1)
GUI for interactive three-way merge),
.B edit
(open conflicted files in the user's editor), or
.B abort
(stop on conflict).
The default is
.B patchpal
if a graphical display and
.BR patchpal (1)
are available, otherwise
.BR edit .
.PP
The
.B patchpal
policy is a key feature for developers who already use
.BR patchpal (1)
for cherry-pick conflict resolution.
The
.B edit
policy opens all conflicted files in the user's preferred editor
(configurable via
.BR \-\-editor ,
session, or
.BR $VISUAL / $EDITOR ;
defaults to
.BR vim ).
.PP
Clean cherry-picks proceed automatically while conflicts
in subsystem files invoke the chosen resolution strategy.
Out-of-scope conflicts (MAINTAINERS, files outside the target
subsystem) are still resolved automatically.
Build failures also present an interactive menu allowing the user
to fix failing files using their resolution strategy, skip the
commit, or abort.
.PP
A
.B dist-configs
build is run inside a toolbox container to validate kernel configs,
with caching so subsequent runs skip the rebuild when HEAD is
unchanged.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Session parameters (prompted interactively or via CLI)"
These are saved to
.I .backport/session.json
and reused across runs.
They can also be provided on the command line to override session values.
.TP
.BI \-\-subsystem " PATH"
Subsystem directory relative to the kernel tree root,
e.g.\&
.IR drivers/char/ipmi .
Used for scope-path auto-discovery and branch naming.
.TP
.BI \-\-rhel " VERSION"
RHEL version (e.g.\&
.BR 9 ", " 10 ", " 10.3 ).
.TP
.BI \-\-upstream\-repo " DIR"
Path to the upstream Linux kernel git repository.
.TP
.BI \-\-upstream\-version " TAG"
Upstream version tag that marks the end of the range,
e.g.\&
.BR v7.1 " or " v7.1\-rc3 .
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-signed\-off\-by " " \fI"NAME <EMAIL>"\fR
Signed-off-by trailer added to every commit message.
.SS "Optional arguments"
.TP
.BI \-\-jira " URL"
JIRA ticket URL.
Default:
.BR RHEL\-PLACEHOLDER .
.TP
.BI \-\-extra\-paths " PATH ..."
Additional scope paths to include alongside the auto-discovered ones.
.TP
.BI \-\-only " PATH ..."
Use only these scope paths and skip auto-discovery entirely.
Useful for catch-up runs on specific directories such as
Documentation or include headers.
.TP
.BI \-\-branch " NAME"
Branch name to create or check out.
Default: the leaf component of the
.B \-\-subsystem
path.
.TP
.BI \-\-output\-dir " DIR"
Output directory for patches, reports, and saved state.
Default:
.IR <rhel\-repo>/../backports/<rhel>/<subsystem>/ .
.TP
.BI \-\-conflict\-policy " POLICY"
How to handle in-scope file conflicts.
Default:
.B patchpal
if a graphical display and patchpal are available, otherwise
.BR edit .
.RS
.TP
.B patchpal
Launch the
.BR patchpal (1)
GUI for interactive three-way merge resolution.
Requires an active graphical display
.RB ( DISPLAY
or
.BR WAYLAND_DISPLAY )
and
.B patchpal
on
.BR PATH .
.TP
.B edit
Open conflicted files in the user's editor for manual resolution.
See
.BR \-\-editor .
.TP
.B abort
Abort the cherry-pick on any in-scope conflict.
.RE
.TP
.BI \-\-editor " CMD"
Editor command for the
.B edit
conflict policy and build-failure fixes.
Saved in the session file.
Default: vim (fallback: vi); also respects
.B $VISUAL
and
.BR $EDITOR .
.TP
.BI \-\-build\-policy " POLICY"
When to run a build test inside the toolbox container.
.RS
.TP
.B conflict
Build only after commits that had conflicts (default).
.TP
.B every
Build after every commit.
.TP
.B none
Never build.
.RE
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Classify and list upstream commits without cherry-picking.
Useful for reviewing what would be applied before committing to a run.
.TP
.B \-\-continue
Resume from previously saved state in the output directory.
.TP
.B \-\-yes
Skip the interactive confirmation menu and proceed immediately.
.TP
.BI \-\-assisted\-by " \"NAME <EMAIL>\""
Assisted-by trailer added to commit messages, e.g.\&
.IR "Claude <no-reply@anthropic.com>" .
.TP
.BI \-\-pick " HASH"
Cherry-pick a single upstream commit (by its full 40-character hash)
onto the current HEAD with conflict resolution and a gort-style
commit message.
Skips the normal multi-commit workflow phases.
.TP
.BI \-\-divergence " HASH"
Upstream commit hash to use as the divergence point, skipping
automatic detection.
.TP
.BI \-\-toolbox " NAME"
Toolbox container name for
.B dist-configs
builds.
Default:
.BI rhel RHEL
(e.g.\&
.BR rhel10 ).
.SH MODES
.SS "Full backport (default)"
Discovers scope paths from the subsystem directory, finds the
divergence point between upstream and RHEL, lists pending
upstream commits, and cherry-picks them in order.
Each commit receives a gort-style message with JIRA, upstream status,
conflict notes, the original commit metadata, and sign-off trailers.
.SS "Single-commit pick (\-\-pick)"
Cherry-picks exactly one upstream commit onto the current HEAD.
The upstream repository is automatically configured as a git remote
if needed, ensuring the commit object is reachable.
Requires
.B \-\-subsystem
for scope-path context.
.SH SESSIONS
.B backport-subsystem
automatically manages a session file at
.I .backport/session.json
in the current repository.
There are no flags to manage sessions; they are handled transparently.
.SS "Interactive mode (no CLI arguments)"
When invoked without session-level arguments on the command line,
an interactive menu is displayed showing all parameters with their
current values (loaded from the saved session, if any).
.PP
Each parameter is labelled with a single\-character hotkey
.RB ( s ", " r ", " u ", " v ", " b ", " j ", " t ", " p ", " c ", " d ", " a ", " o ", " e ).
Press a key to edit that parameter.
All menu input is single\-keypress (no Enter required).
.PP
Press
.B g
to accept all values and proceed (Go).
If required fields (marked with
.BR * )
are not set,
.B g
will refuse and list what is missing.
Press
.B q
to abort.
.PP
When editing a field, type a new value and press Enter.
Press Enter on an empty line to keep the current value,
or type
.B clear
to remove an optional field.
The
.B toolbox
field presents a numbered list of available toolbox containers
(from
.BR "toolbox list" )
for single\-keypress selection.
.SS "Command-line mode"
When session-level arguments are provided on the command line,
they are merged into the saved session silently, with no
interactive menu.
This allows scripted and non\-interactive usage.
.SS "Sticky parameters"
All session parameters carry their values across invocations
as defaults in the interactive menu.
.SS "Transient flags"
.BR \-\-dry\-run ", " \-\-pick ", " \-\-continue ", " \-\-yes ", and "
.B \-\-divergence
are per-invocation and never saved to the session.
.SH EXAMPLES
First run (prompts for session parameters):
.PP
.RS
.nf
cd ~/kernels/centos\-9
backport-subsystem \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Subsequent runs reuse the session automatically:
.PP
.RS
.nf
backport-subsystem
backport-subsystem \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.RE
.PP
Pick a single upstream commit (session provides the rest):
.PP
.RS
.nf
backport-subsystem \-\-pick a8aebe93a4938c0ca1941eeaae821738f869be3d
.fi
.RE
.PP
Interactive conflict resolution with patchpal:
.PP
.RS
.nf
backport-subsystem \-\-conflict\-policy patchpal
.fi
.RE
.PP
Override a session value for one run:
.PP
.RS
.nf
backport-subsystem \-\-upstream\-version v7.2
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All commits applied successfully (or dry-run completed).
.TP
.B 1
An error occurred: invalid arguments, git failures, unresolvable
conflicts, build failures, or missing prerequisites.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .backport/session.json
Automatic session file storing parameters and metadata.
.TP
.I .backport\-dist\-configs\-head
Stamp file in the RHEL repo tracking the HEAD hash for
.B dist-configs
caching.
.TP
.I <output\-dir>/state.json
Saved state for
.B \-\-continue
resumption.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rhel\-upstream\-diff (1),
.BR patchpal (1),
.BR git\-cherry\-pick (1),
.BR toolbox (1)
